                    </ab>
                
                 </div>
               <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" resp="#POC" source="MAC1945">
                   <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName><unclear reason="worn">A</unclear>V<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/>S<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"
                        /><unclear reason="worn">S</unclear><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown"/><w type="formula" lemma="maqqas"><unclear reason="worn">M</unclear>AQ</w><gap reason="lost"
                        extent="unknown"/>VS</persName>
                   </ab>                   
                   <ab type="list">AV[---]S[---]S[---]MAQ[---]VS</ab>
            </div> 
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                <app n="1">
                    <note>The initial A, the second S and the M are unclear.</note>
                </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">                 
                    <p>[...] son of [...]</p>                
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The presence of MAQ might indicate that this inscription may have contained a common formula word found in the ogham corpus: MAQI 'son'.</p>                
            </div>
